---
import BlogPostLayout from '../../../layouts/BlogPostLayout.astro';

const title = "Ranking Every Halo Wars 2 Map";
const description = "A comprehensive tier list ranking of all multiplayer maps in Halo Wars 2, from S-tier Sentry to F-tier Fort Jordan. Includes Blitz and Terminus Firefight maps.";
const category = "Reviews";
const publishedDate = "February 2, 2026";
const dateIso = "2026-02-02";
const tags = ["Halo Wars 2"];
const ogImage = "/content/blog/reviews-placeholder.svg";
---

<BlogPostLayout
  title={title}
  description={description}
  category={category}
  publishedDate={publishedDate}
  dateIso={dateIso}
  ogImage={ogImage}
  tags={tags}
  youtubeId="sZS6g6Ui9Ak"
>
  <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed mb-6">
    A comprehensive ranking of all multiplayer maps in Halo Wars 2, including Fort Jordan, the Battlegrounds map for Blitz Firefight, and Terminus Firefight.
  </p>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 text-cyan-300">S Tier</h2>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Sentry</h3>
  <p class="mb-4">Not only the best Halo Wars 2 map, but the <strong>best Halo Wars map between both games</strong>:</p>
  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Map designed for turtling - given to Team Respawn for the sole purpose of turtling</li>
    <li>Two tiers of highly defendable bases with height advantage</li>
    <li>Can take center node for line of sight against air</li>
    <li>Works best with two tiers, UNSC or Banished or double Banished combo</li>
    <li>Can hold Sentry with four starting bases (your base, teammate's base, and two X-Bows)</li>
    <li>Don't need any other expansion bases on the entire map</li>
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Featured in Super Turtle playlist</strong>, including a five and a half hour game</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 mt-8 text-cyan-300">A Tier</h2>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Badlands</h3>
  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Favors turtling (not as much as Sentry)</li>
    <li>Expo base is in the middle between you and your teammate</li>
    <li>Position is both highly defendable and easy to attack</li>
    <li>Can still fly across from bottom for vulture spam</li>
    <li>Need to be prepared if you overextend</li>
    <li>Overall really great map</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Mirage</h3>
  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>One of the free DLC maps (Fissures and Mirage)</li>
    <li>One of the more sweaty maps because it's so small</li>
    <li>2v2 map that's more arena-based</li>
    <li>Great for grudge matches or 1v1/2v2</li>
    <li>Requires tactical play and careful control of the center</li>
    <li>Very easy to lose if not careful - hard to come back once momentum is lost</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Rift</h3>
  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Higher skill ceiling players and tournaments favor Rift</li>
    <li>Great for grudge matches and tournaments</li>
    <li>Similar to Mirage - requires strategic thinking</li>
    <li>Lots of minis that can be stolen</li>
    <li>Design that should be seen more often in Halo Wars 2 maps</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Vault</h3>
  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Has scaling problems like Frontier - cutoff parts in smaller player counts</li>
    <li>Much better map in 3v3 - barren areas in 2v2 that don't make sense</li>
    <li>Center power node has teleporters that jump you to other side</li>
    <li>Can get great turtles on Vault if you get a line down across center of map</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Terminus Firefight</h3>
  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Only one map added to Terminus Firefight</li>
    <li>Enjoyable game mode with many options</li>
    <li>Problem is lack of maps (same as Blitz) - would be better with more variety</li>
    <li>Enjoyable for first-time players</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 mt-8 text-cyan-300">B Tier</h2>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Fissures</h3>
  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>One of the free DLC maps - many people don't like it</li>
    <li>In 3v3, it's almost biased with 2v2 and 1v1 battle sets</li>
    <li>Expo is right in the middle between both sides</li>
    <li>Favors good teamwork and coordination</li>
    <li>Towers and covers provide great line of sight against air spam</li>
    <li>Nothing that makes this map epic - just a general map</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Frontier</h3>
  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Map with mixed experiences - great games and bad games</li>
    <li>Designed for largest audience (3v3), then cuts off parts for 2v2</li>
    <li>Can see cutoff parts with camera and get stuck</li>
    <li>Really like the healing spires on Frontier - placed almost out of the way</li>
    <li>Nothing all that awesome about Frontier</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Bedrock</h3>
  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Awesome map that really shines in 3v3</li>
    <li>Great for leaders that favor siege (Anders and Pavium)</li>
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Great triple Pavium super turtle</strong></li>
    <li>Way map is designed might be better in 2v2 than 3v3</li>
    <li>In 2v2, really focused in middle with four bases</li>
    <li>Great symmetrical map</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 mt-8 text-cyan-300">C Tier</h2>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Ashes</h3>
  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Falls victim to teleporters (like Highway)</li>
    <li>Teleporters ruin all the fun that would otherwise be a great map</li>
    <li>Teleporters take you behind someone's other base - easy for vulture spam to snipe base</li>
    <li>Completely dead area on one side with forerunner ramp - waste of space</li>
    <li>Easier to defend against teleporters on Ashes than Highway</li>
    <li>Can cheese with leader powers if someone goes through teleporter</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 mt-8 text-cyan-300">D Tier</h2>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Highway</h3>
  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Sole reason for D-tier: the teleporters</strong></li>
    <li>Teleporters absolutely ruin this map</li>
    <li>Map is way too long - takes forever with slow-moving vehicles like Scorpions</li>
    <li>Have to go through teleporters because it takes so long to traverse</li>
    <li>Would be great map if teleporters weren't there</li>
    <li>Teleporters go perpendicular - always jumps to other side</li>
    <li>Can use teleporters to steal minis at beginning of game</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Battlegrounds (Blitz Map)</h3>
  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Only one map for entire Blitz game mode</li>
    <li>Blitz would have been better without microtransactions</li>
    <li>More thought needed with deck design and card collection</li>
    <li>Weird thing: can see through fog of war on this map all the time</li>
    <li>Not sure if intentional or not - noticed in beta and at launch</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 mt-8 text-cyan-300">F Tier</h2>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Fort Jordan</h3>
  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Map added entirely out of already used Halo Wars 2 assets - no new assets</li>
    <li>Meant to be gift to Halo Wars team and community - hyped up greatly when first came out</li>
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Map is way too big</strong> - not scaled properly</li>
    <li>Takes all afternoon to go from one side to other</li>
    <li>Often see people just playing air game because that's only way to navigate map</li>
    <li>Same size map no matter if playing 1v1, 2v2, or 3v3 (very different from other maps)</li>
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Lots of technical problems</strong>: black screen, no ground visible, base doesn't spawn sometimes</li>
    <li>Appreciate gesture of bringing back beloved Halo Wars 1 map (Fort Dean), but Fort Jordan isn't it</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 mt-8 text-cyan-300">Summary</h2>

  <p class="mb-4">Here's the complete tier ranking of all Halo Wars 2 maps:</p>

  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">S Tier:</strong> Sentry</li>
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">A Tier:</strong> Badlands, Mirage, Rift, Vault, Terminus Firefight</li>
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">B Tier:</strong> Fissures, Frontier, Bedrock</li>
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">C Tier:</strong> Ashes</li>
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">D Tier:</strong> Highway, Battlegrounds</li>
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">F Tier:</strong> Fort Jordan</li>
  </ul>

  <p class="mb-4 mt-6">
    Halo Wars 2 has map variety, but not as great as Halo Wars 1. Only one banger (Sentry) and a lot of maps need some work. That said, Halo Wars 2 maps are at least fun and enjoyable for new players and returning players to this day. Halo Wars 1 maps are almost all S or A tier - they're just so good.
  </p>

</BlogPostLayout>
